Okay so we spent a week in Oahu and ate the local traditional Hawaiian food for the majority of our stay. You know, the spam musubi, shrimp, poke, fish, coconut (yeah I broke one open and attempted to eat it), rice, egg, spam, spam, spam...Joking aside, we love spam, so good. We tried to stay away from fast food restaurants. We strived to eat only authentic Hawaiian. Anyways, we felt like we were spam-loving-born-on-the-island Hawaiians by our third day in Oahu. Then we encountered Hank's. Our mainland cravings kicked in for fast food. But we soon realized that Hank's isn't fast food. Yes, it may be fast to get your order, but this isn't traditional fast food. It is very much original, it is very much local, it is very much authentic, American, and most importantly, it is very much Hawaiian.

This place is great for both kids and kids at heart.  I haven't ventured outside of their Chicago Dog simply because it is REALLY GOOD!  The dogs themselves have that fantastic 'snap!' when you bite into them. Their fries are also top notch - not quite steak fries, but not thin fast food fries either - cooked to perfection.  They sell a number of special dipping sauces.  We got the Garlic Aioli which was nice, but these fries were pretty perfect sans sauce too. There's an off-the-menu option the man at the counter offered for our kids which would just be a basic naked hotdog, but the kids (5 & 7) were happy with Hank's Frank - basic dog with mustard, relish, onion and pickle. Onion Rings are skippable, not much batter on them and they were pretty limp - happy that we got both those and the fries. The only difficulties are the seating (all counter-top) and eating out of the boxes makes for a challenge to catch the goodies as they fall out when you bite into the dogs.

Takes the idea of a hotdog and makes it entirely unique. Hank’s is a great afternoon lunch spot. With an adequate amount of outside seating I have never had trouble finding a spot. This is a fairly popular place so I would try to avoid going during the lunch rush because Hanks is very popular. The hot dog list is very broad, with many options to choose from. So far I have only had two of there dogs, and both were very well prepared with excellent flavor. My favorite factor of this restaurant is that they have daily specials featuring even more unique options such as their lobster hot dog or their wild boar dog. Another thing I judge burger and hotdog places on are their fries, and Hanks makes some good fries. You can go with more traditional French fries or their double fried option for extra crisp. Moving to Hawaii I never would have expected to find good hotdogs, and Hanks proved me wrong. Enjoy!

Will definitely be going back.

Delicious, cheap and quick. We were there on a Sunday and the place was empty. Free parking next door and delicious food. Had the Hawaiian dog which was sweet and vinegary and juicy. Get the pineapple ice.

Great hot dogs. I know some mention it is pricey, bit for Honolulu, it wasn't too bad.  We got three different specialty hotdogs, an order of onion rings and two hibiscus lemonades for $35 ish. The Polish dog was my favorite, grilled onions cooked perfectly. Hawaiian dog came in second.  I believe they validate parking as well (for an hour) at the shopping center they are located in, which I wish I knew. We ended up street parking further away and walking.
Pineapple ice, curry ketchup and any hotdog or sausage on the menu!
Service was very friendly and timely. Food was delicious and a good portion for the price. A variety of choices on the menu makes for a good place to come multiple times.

Excellent hotdogs and amazing fries! Only downside is that their hours are a little wacky.

I had the weekend special here (lobster fat boy + fries/drink). It was a very good dog, respectable French fries and an overall tasty meal. Although, if I am going to pay $17 for a meal and $0.99 for refills then it is not going to be for a hot dog and French fries that's not too dissimilar from what you could make at home. Not much parking either and tow trucks patrol the area.
